node.text:
When I was a kid I had seizures. As I got older, I accumulated a basket-full of random symptoms, from seasonal allergies, to eczema, constipation, hormonal imbalances, and massive fatigue. Many of you are aware of my autoimmune diagnosis from blog posts and videos, but today I'm rewinding ALL the way back, to tell you #MyWholeStory (with a few baby photos, and mom cameo for good measure 😉).

I'm thrilled to partner with @Vitamix on today's video, and grateful that they're elevating individual wellness stories. There's so much that we can learn from each other! In fact, it was because of hearing someone else's wellness story years ago that I was able to connect the dots on my own body, and ultimately get tested for celiac disease.

You guys know I'm pretty obsessed with Vitamix, and it's because a decade ago I purchased my first Vitamix blender (as a little motivation to myself) to adopt healthier habits. Today, that 750 Pro blender is still going strong (my mom has it now!), and my A3500 blender gets used almost daily in my kitchen, blending up smoothies, soups, nut butters, hummus, and more! Looking back, that simple purchase played such a pivotal role in my wellness journey, and I'm confident it will play an equally positive role in your life. So today, to celebrate Vitamix's amazing 100 year anniversary, I'm happy to give away a Vitamix A3500 blender to one of YOU!

To enter: comment below (or on the YouTube video) and let me know how a Vitamix blender would inspire healthy habits in your kitchen! I'll select one winner (at random) on my birthday - August 31, 2021! *open to those 18 years and older from US, UK, Canada, Australia, and New Zealand.

#VitamixPartner #Vitamix #vitamix100ways #wholebeginshere

node.text: It's always lovely to start the week with cookies! 😉 These gluten-free, paleo-friendly chocolate chips cookies are made with simple ingredients like almond flour, coconut sugar, eggs, coconut oil (or butter if you'd like), and a hefty amount of chocolate chips. I'm kinda kicking myself that I didn't save any from my last batch and freeze them (I may have pigged out a little too much 😂)... as I'd really love one right now. Maybe I'll have to make another batch later this week. Oh, I also saw several comments asking if I had a nut-free chocolate chip cookie recipe. I don't have one right now, but I'm always happy to add one in the future. Unfortunately, it's not easy to just replace flours in gluten-free recipes...other ratios always need to be tweaked, thus lots of testing. So if that's something you'd like to see in the future, let me know below. Happy Monday! 🤗

node.title: The BEST Gluten-Free Chocolate Chip Cookies

I’m a big fan of shrimp recipes, but these shrimp tacos might just be my favorite! When I was a kid I had seizures. As I got older, I accumulated a basket-full of random symptoms, from seasonal allergies, to eczema, constipation, hormonal imbalances, and massive fatigue. Many of you are aware of my autoimmune diagnosis from blog posts and videos, but today I'm rewinding ALL the way back, to tell you #MyWholeStory (with a few baby photos, and mom cameo for good measure 😉).

I'm thrilled to partner with @Vitamix on today's video, and grateful that they're elevating individual wellness stories. There's so much that we can learn from each other! In fact, it was because of hearing someone else's wellness story years ago that I was able to connect the dots on my own body, and ultimately get tested for celiac disease.

You guys know I'm pretty obsessed with Vitamix, and it's because a decade ago I purchased my first Vitamix blender (as a little motivation to myself) to adopt healthier habits. Today, that 750 Pro blender is still going strong (my mom has it now!), and my A3500 blender gets used almost daily in my kitchen, blending up smoothies, soups, nut butters, hummus, and more! Looking back, that simple purchase played such a pivotal role in my wellness journey, and I'm confident it will play an equally positive role in your life. So today, to celebrate Vitamix's amazing 100 year anniversary, I'm happy to give away a Vitamix A3500 blender to one of YOU!

To enter: comment below (or on the YouTube video) and let me know how a Vitamix blender would inspire healthy habits in your kitchen! I'll select one winner (at random) on my birthday - August 31, 2021! *open to those 18 years and older from US, UK, Canada, Australia, and New Zealand.

#VitamixPartner #Vitamix #vitamix100ways #wholebeginshere

This Greek Sheet Pan Chicken is AMAZING. I’m obsessed with it and I think you will be too. 😍 And here’s the funny thing, historically I haven’t been a fan of sheet pan meals. When I’ve made other recipes in the past I’ve had lackluster results, with either the chicken drying out or the veggies ending up undercooked. The key is correctly combining the right ingredients on the sheet pan so that everything cooks at the same rate. And today’s Greek sheet pan chicken dinner does just that!! You’ve got juicy chicken, caramelized veggies, and the best Greek flavors all in one dish. So. Darn. Good. Now go watch the new video and let me know what you think! 🤗
.
Recipe: https://downshiftology.com/recipes/greek-sheet-pan-chicken/

Slow roasted salmon with a citrusy fennel orange topping. 🤩 This salmon recipe is incredibly moist and fall-apart tender (swipe to see the photo!) and it’s virtually impossible to overcook, thanks to the low temperature. So it you have a tendency to overcook your fish, this may be the salmon recipe for you! And the topping is a simple mix of fennel, orange, fresh herbs, lemon, and honey. It’s sweet, citrusy, light n’ fresh, and the perfect summer dinner! Give it a try. 🤗
.
Recipe: https://downshiftology.com/recipes/slow-roasted-salmon-fennel-orange/

node.text: I did a 9 mile mountain bike trail today!! I’ve taken my bike out a few times, but this was the first legit mountain bike trail with single lane tracks, loads of bumps, sharp turns and drops, and fast speed. And I’m SO happy to report that I didn’t crash or fall off once (though not gonna lie, I’m actually surprised I didn’t eat it in a few spots 😂). My bro and his family are much more expert at these trails, so I’m pretty darn happy with my performance this morning. But yeah, I think I’ll be waddling and limping a bit tomorrow from sore muscles. Lol. Happy Saturday! What are you guys up to today? Doing anything fun? 🚴 PS - I’ll show a little more trail fun on stories.

NEW!! Look at this beauty! It’s a refreshing cucumber radish salad that’s perfect for hot summer days. ☀️ Just grab Persian cucumbers instead of English cucumbers (they’re the same size as the radishes!), then use a mandoline or knife to quickly slice them up. Add them to a bowl along with thinly sliced green onion, chopped dill, a simple lemon dressing, salt and pepper… then stir! Enjoy it as a side salad, a healthy snack or layer it on your morning avocado toast! Enjoy! 🤗
.
Recipe: https://downshiftology.com/recipes/cucumber-radish-salad/
